Apoidea Group is an AI-empowered Fintech company. As the founding business of Apoidea, Apoidea Media provides content marketing services to financial institutions. We own 4 media pages - Market Digest, Business Digest, Health Concept, and Beauty Digest and run other financial institution client pages. Apoidea Media has been serving a large proportion of active Equity Derivative Product Issuers in Hong Kong.




We are looking for a passionate Social Media Executive to manage and create content for our Business Digest and Market Digest Instagram pages. 




Job Description:


Manage and create content for the social media accounts (especially on Instagram), including copywriting and image creating/editing;
Closely monitor social media channels for timely response to comments and inquiries from audiences;
Develop and lead all video content, including but not limited to script development, storyboarding, concept, editing, etc.
Ensures contents are original, accurate and fact-based Editorial in driving concept development and content direction for editorial projects;
Support the marketing team with English/Chinese language proofreading, editing, copywriting, original content creation and content vetting, etc.

Requirements:

Good knowledge or experience in copywriting;
Degree Holder in Design, Marketing, Business, E-commerce or related disciplines;
Experience in using Photoshop, Illustrator, Powerpoint, other design softwares will be a good plus; 
1 year of relevant experience in marketing, social media production, preferable in e-commerce industries will be a good plus while fresh graduates will also be considered; 
Familiar with various social media platforms (Facebook, Instagram, Youtube, and etc.);
Passionate, responsible, and flexible to be a part of the cross-functional team;
Excellent communication skills and strong problem-solving skills, able to work both independently and as a team;
Good command of spoken and written Chinese and English.

RESPONSIBILITIES:

Creative advertising headlines and smart copy for efficient marketing works.
Work with the team of creatives to come up with great creative ideas.
Understand the interactive and integrated marketing mechanism, can participate in the planning stage creative thinking and copy writing.
Be responsible for the proposal and planning of brand projects, participate in the creation of the discussion, with the implementation of the relevant documents;
Responsible for the customer's campaign, hot topics creative discussions, and creative thinking and creative projects;

REQUIREMNETS:

1 to 4 years working experience in copy;
Good understanding of ATL, digital and BTL;
Good at all kinds of content, style of copywriting, skilled use of office software.
Active thinking, good communication skills, enthusiasm and sense of responsibility, and team spirit;

Benefits:

5 days Work + Bank Holidays
Full Medical Coverage
Performance Bonus
Birthday Leave, Wedding Leave
Training Subsidy
Professional Training + Good Career Prospect in the Growing Digital Marketing Industry

Responsibilities include:

Craft creative copy writing across social media platform;
Support creative project pitching;
Assist online marketing execution team to plan and implement of digital marketing communication/programs to build brand awareness;
Work with internal teams to ensure content for internal and external communication are published in the right channels;
Develop and edit content / copy for online customer communications;
Perform quality control on all advertisements and content distribution; track monthly performance data.

Requirements :

Passionate in digital is a MUST;
Diploma holder majoring in Journalism, Marketing, communications or PR related discipline or above;
1 year of relevant work experience in publishing, editing or copywriting; experience in digital marketing agencies is a plus.
Experience in creative project pitching is an advantage;
Excellent in Chinese and English written skill;
To be responsible, organized, proactive and self-motivated.
Candidates with more experience will be considered as Senior Copywriter.

