Responsibilities:
assist in developing creative contents for social media, including but not limited to website, social media (Facebook, Instagram, WeChat, Weibo, etc.);
assist in initiating marketing and PR activities to drive traffic for the online platforms;
assist in brand building activities in the mainland China market;
be responsible to the content development and management of the University website for mainland China target audience;
participate in University promotion and student recruitment activities in mainland China if necessary;
provide support in organising CPAO events / activities / exhibitions / ceremonies / conferences; and
liaise and coordinate with internal staff and outside parties such as media reporter / advertising agency / school representatives for CPAO / advertising campaigns or school talks.

Applicants should:
possess a recognised university degree, preferably in communication, public relations, journalism, business, marketing, advertising or other related disciplines;
have at least 1 year of work experience in public relations, corporate communications, social media, publications relating activities, event management, marketing or brand building;
have experience in digital marketing and video production;
have good knowledge and practical experience in graphic design software;
have effective administrative, communication and social media skills;
preferably have experience in website content development and management;
preferably have brand promotion experience in mainland China;
have excellent command of written and spoken English and Chinese (including Mandarin); and
be well-organised, a good team player and able to handle multi-tasks efficiently.

Working outside normal office hours may be required.
